NAME
	send_message - send a message to a user

SYNOPSIS
	void send_message(string message)
	void send_message(int echo)


DESCRIPTION
	In the first form, send a message to the user associated with the
	current object.  In the second form, input echoing for the user will
	be turned off or on, the value of echo being zero or non-zero,
	respectively.  If the current object is not associated with a user,
	nothing will happen.
	When used by the driver object, send_message() will echo the message
	on stderr.

SEE ALSO
	kfun/query_ip_number, kfun/this_user, kfun/users
